The easy way:

```java
public static byte[] toJpegBytes(BufferedImage image) throws IOException {
  ByteArrayOutputStream baos = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
  ImageIO.write(image, &quot;jpeg&quot;, baos);
  return baos.toByteArray();
}
```

If you want more control over the conversion (compression level, etc) see [Setting jpg compression level with ImageIO in Java](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/17108234/setting-jpg-compression-level-with-imageio-in-java).

